                <p>Observe that the form of the relationship between the 1,500 meter race's winning
                    time and the year is linear. The least squares regression line is therefore an
                    appropriate way to summarize the relationship and examine the change in winning
                    times over the course of the last century. We will now find the least squares
                    regression line and plot it on a scatterplot. </p>
                <pullout>
