                        <alternative value="r">
                            <title>R Instructions</title>
                            <p>In order to fit the regression line, we use the command
                                    <code>lm()</code>. The <code>lm()</code> command produces a
                                large amount of information, which we will want to extract as we
                                need it, so we save the information to another variable name model.
                                To do this in R, copy the command:</p>
                            <code>model = lm(olym$Time~olym$Year)</code>
                            <p>To add the regression line to the scatterplot, we can extract the
                                linear equation from model and add the line to the scatterplot. To
                                do this in R, copy the entire command below:</p>
                            <ul style="none">
                                <li><code>plot(olym$Year, olym$Time, xlab="Year of Olympic Games",
                                        ylab="Winning Time of 1500m Race
                                        (secs)");abline(model)</code></li>

                            </ul>



                            <p>We can also extract the y-intercept and slope from the model to
                                determine the regression equation, to do this in R, copy the
                                command:</p>
                            <code>coef(model)</code>


                            <!--<p>Do not close the graphics window in R. You are going to add features
                                to the existing graphics window. To add the regression line, copy
                                these commands: </p>
                            <code> L = lm(olym$Time~olym$Year); </code>
                            <code>abline(L);</code>
                            <p> The next commands print the regression equation on the graph: </p>
                            <code>cf=coefficients(L);</code>
                            <code> legend(1940,260,legend=paste("time =
                                ",round(cf[1],0),round(cf[2],2),"year")) </code>
                            <p><em>Note: Using R</em>&#8212;The command "lm" calculates a large
                                number of parameters related to linear regression but does not
                                display them. The commands "abline" and "cf" extract information
                                from the results of "lm" to draw the regression line and print the
                                coefficients of the regression equation. </p>-->
                        </alternative>
