                        <alternative value="ti">
                            <title>TI Instructions</title>
                            <p><em>Linear Regression Line (Line of Best
                                Fit)&#8212;calculate</em></p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Choose <code style="inline">STAT/CALC/8:LinReg(a+bx).
                                    </code></li>
                                <li>You’ll see:<code style="inline"> LinReg(a+bx)</code></li>
                                <li>Choose the <code>Xlist</code> and <code>Ylist</code>. Since the
                                    Year data is in L1 and the Time data is in L2, enter
                                        <code>2nd/1</code> after <code>Xlist</code>. Enter
                                        <code>2nd/2</code> after <code>Ylist</code>. Leave
                                        <code>FreqList</code> and <code>Store RegEQ</code>
                                    blank.</li>
                                <li>Highlight <code>Calculate</code> and press
                                    <code>ENTER</code></li>

                            </ul>
                            <p>You should now see:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>LinReg</li>
                                <li>y=a+bx</li>
                                <li>a=</li>
                                <li>b=</li>
                                <li>r<sup>2</sup>=</li>
                                <li>r=</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>The regression line is given as:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>y=a+bx</li>
                                <li>a=</li>
                                <li>b=</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>where a is the Y intercept of the regression line and b is the slope
                                of the regression line.</p>
                            <p>Now let's plot this line on the scatterplot.</p>
                            <p><em>Linear Regression Line (Line of Best Fit)&#8212;plot on
                                    scatterplot</em></p>
                            <p>The TI calculator stores the last regression line that you calculated
                                until you calculate another one. </p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Choose <code style="inline">Y=</code></li>
                                <li>Now you need to cut and paste the values for <code
                                        style="inline">a</code> and <code style="inline">b</code>: <ul>
                                        <li>To get the Y intercept (a): <ul>
                                                <li>Choose <code style="inline"
                                                  >VARS/5:Statistics.</code></li>
                                                <li>Choose <code style="inline">EQ</code> (right
                                                  arrow twice).</li>
                                                <li>Choose <code style="inline">2:a</code></li>
                                            </ul></li>
                                        <li>Press the <code style="inline">+</code> button.</li>
                                        <li>To get the slope (b): <ul>
                                                <li>Choose <code style="inline"
                                                  >VARS/5:Statistics</code>.</li>
                                                <li>Choose <code style="inline">EQ</code> (right
                                                  arrow twice).</li>
                                                <li>Choose <code style="inline">3:b</code></li>
                                            </ul></li>
                                    </ul></li>
                                <li>Press the <code style="inline">X, T, &#920;, n</code>
                                    button.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>You should see: <image style="inline"
                                    src="../../webcontent/linear8lbd3.jpg"/></p>
                            <p>Note: As long as you don’t change <code style="inline">Y1</code>,
                                each time you find another regression line, a and b will
                                automatically be saved with the new values and the new line will be
                                graphed.</p>
                            <p>You can toggle <code style="inline">Y1</code> on and off. When the
                                "=" is highlighted, the graph is ON. To turn it OFF, use the left
                                arrow to highlight the "=," then press <code style="inline"
                                    >ENTER</code>. Repeat to turn the graph back on.</p>
                            <p>If you’ve set up the scatterplot and set up <code style="inline"
                                    >Y1=</code>, you can <code style="inline">ZOOM/9:ZoomStat</code>
                                to see the regression line plotted on the scatterplot.</p>
                            <p>You should see a graph window with the scatterplot and the regression
                                plotted on it. Choose <code style="inline">TRACE</code> and then use
                                the up and down arrows to toggle between the line of best fit and
                                the scatterplot. Use the left and right arrows to see each
                                individual data pair on the scatterplot.</p>
                        </alternative>
                    </alternatives>

                </pullout>
            </body>
        </section>
